	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was under the impression that <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_pattern_tables" class="postlink">NES</a> and <a href="http://gbdev.gg8.se/wiki/articles/Video_Display#VRAM_Tile_Data" class="postlink">GB</a> had the exact same CHR format: 2bpp planar, d7 leftmost;<br />LSB line 1, MSB line 1, LSB line 2, etc.<br /><br />I'm curious what needs converting?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Thu Feb 26, 2015 1:15 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Does a working NES2GB and GB2NES CHR converter exist?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />On the NES, the bitplanes are separated by 8 bytes. On the GB, they're only separated by 1 byte.<br /><br />The &quot;only&quot; difference is ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP vs AIBJCKDLEMFNGOHP

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


